<br>
What a waste of space and bandwith, not tomention we could have had more high level places to go. <br>
<br>
I see more cats running around in WC, LOIO, and the old world zones / Kunark more than I see them in any of the SoL lowbie zones. Why were these even put in the game when the zones we already have are not even close to being utilized. Go into Unrest, Droga, Nurga, Kaesora, any of the countless and un-used 10-40 dungeons and landscapes. Than when you are running past a zone to get to the Grey for some XP, look at how few people there are in these areas. Again, great places to hunt, but were tey needed seeing as they are revamping older dungeons everyday because no one goes to them? <br>
<br>
Mid level armor quests which are barely a step above the class quests already in place. Why even waste the man power for these? I doubt anyone is going to do these quests when if they want armor they can do the quests they already know, much less most lowbies seem to be twinks these days and already place better items on their twinks. Again another useless addition and waste of team development. <br>
<br>
The new graphics. Some appear to be very nice yes. But still lightyears beyond what any game out there is going to have. Much less terrible programming and shotty performance even on high end machines. <br>
<br>
SoL went through the same thing DAOC went through. The expansion was in development for well over 12 months with the idea that all the items were going to be trivial loot. For some un-canny reason people at verant thought we needed more low end content. Why? The low end content we have now isn't even being used while high end guilds and even high end pick up raids are now looking for something to do. There are 3 high end raiding zones (Arguably - as I see it only two that are ever being used)  in SoL with about 10 lowbie areas and 3-4 decent level 55-60 xp and AAXP areas.  When will verant say &quot;Time to revamp the underutilized in SoL - which will be al of them.&quot;<br>
<br>
So on to the next expansion. Yes right now they do not know whether to start EQ 2, (Waiting on what happens with AC 2 and how it goes when their customer base is going to have to start over if they play the new game), or go ahead with a high end raid expansion in which every zone in the new expansion will be detailed high end XP and high end raid encounters. &quot;(Thank god its about time). Where all high end guilds will have a choice of where to go without too much hassle. As it stands now, you have ToV, Kael, SSRA temple, Vex Thal (When you can get into it), Sleepers if you have a key, Veeshans peak which is a push over and no challenge at all these days. Meanwhile we have about 60+ lowbie zones which for some idiotic reason verant thought we needed more, when we never saw half of them being used in the first place. <br>
<br>
I knew about the idea on the table for an all inclusive high level raiding expansion. But in talking about it I didn't know that there was another idea for the young new hot shot dev team. Making a sequel to Everquest that will force you to start over. have fun on that leveling treadmill again - but what they do not know if a lot of people will never start over. They will move on to a new game. <br>
<br>
They better buck up and listen to what I think they should have publicized in the first place.  Players in Everquest, at least all the ones I have talked to, are not going to start over. This is an MMORPG - an expanding world. You give it another graphics make over, you increase the monthly rate if you have to, (although I know they are making a killing as it is), you add high end content and enough with this low end bullshit that no one cares about. The end game is being played by over 50% of the server. We need more things to do - and adding a new style of fire beetles and new gimp lowbie quests for our twinks isn't going to cut the butter even if you had a hot knife. <br>
<br>
Make sure you let Verant know before it is too late.  Because right now you have about 20+ new bright eyed dev's all looking for make a rep for themselves by creating a new game while not even paying attention to the time people in EQ have spent on the current one. <br>
<br>
MMORPG's are just that. Expanding and always continuing. NEVER ending. Expand the story, expand the zones, tell different tales, create new worlds in the same genre - But make a new game entirely, and you might make a new rep for yourself alright...  <br>
<br>
&quot;I made a game no one gave two shits about&quot;<br>
