<br>
When I raise new characters I try to do so in zones where my other characters didn't play.   In the lowest levels, I found Shar Vahl, Shadeweaver's Thicket, and Paludal caverns to be much more fun than the Antonica and Faydwer zones where my other guys grew up.  <br>
<br>
We've already had a few threads here dedicated to the clustering of players in the LOIO->FM->OT->DL level treadmill, and I think SOE recognized that and tried to provide an alternative.   The miserable attendance in the Luclin zones tells me that they didn't provide a good enough alternative, or possibly they didn't provide an alternative that most peoples' computers and connections can take them to, but I'm glad they tried.<br>
<br>
I think Luclin was designed to encourage players to break out of some of the patterns that they believe - right or wrong - are damaging to the game.   <br>
1) twinking: they tried to provide new zones where players can advance and earn new gear on their own<br>
2) overcrowding/undercrowding:  they tried to design new zones that have similar appeal to the most popular Kunark zones (I think Dawnshroud feels very similar to LOIO, and Marus Seru feels very similar to Overthere)<br>
3) high level burnout: they tried to make it appealing to start and play new characters as an alternative to playing your highest one exclusively for its fourth year<br>
<br>
It is a shame that they didn't do a great job in meeting these goals, and that they dedicated so much of the last expansion to trying to meet them at the expense of high level players.   However, I don't think that they were wrong to try. <p>Regenspieler Stormsong<br>
